eul2N3Qp3b-66xIkYVHwg5PywWRRcWnn_NvHaepa5sTgKPyfNc_AseM2rpLnXy1rdrzrxtBgUdnNSl1DYUuxXKiOJt3hMulzPUrM9sYQdsBtbsomN_j3Bp8KuK-6Yqs0EEs9UJ3s6dXhVy3CakruAcp63F8gTTXtZ_pdqigtDRQhgQcME3ufsjTMWXE7M2eqfdgC7hxJdrLRUTZRlo6xomEzHHkuM1cYxXDyFJth1YHIgHh0K6vnbQMo04j-VIHor73zR0DW9hDkU7vQmbvPuTr3o0n5dE9r-hQWcz_9fqPEFhUqZqd0BWXgy4DG8y47ppLl3zq4_doISptrFmIQa6AqSYqQ6BJkrem24OFyGk6D5FLM7R_yAt6X-ugK3APUwxO10kTzQp04Ez02x8LBHP9FsoSk7Bo=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring module implementation**\\n\\nI’m pondering whether I need a module-info file, especially since the ModuleDescriptor has certain properties but might not lead to a module-info class. The built-in loader could ask for specific classes, like HiddenService.class. I think about implementing a SimpleModuleReader to return bytes for the class. To get those bytes, I consider using ByteBuddy since it’s already a dependency. Should I define a public class with a specific method?\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering dynamic module creation**\\n\\nI’m exploring the dynamic module creation, starting with test fixtures that's exercised via Mockito's public API. If I’m working with Native Image, there’s a chance the ByteBuddy dynamic generation might fail and raise an UnsupportedFeature Error. It seems wise to encompass everything in a try block. I need to generate class bytes, define the module, and I’m facing a potential hurdle regarding ModuleDescriptor packages that includes \\\"sample.hidden\\\" without exports. I’m wondering if I can use URI.create(\\\"memory:///mockito.test.module\\\") for the ModuleReference location.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_KhOg83bTXCKp7ymyaoEzCjqG|fc_05eaf4290c8a1a6b016a21ac25d8dc819387e1487d4d1f7404", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_mockito.mockito_core;\n\nimport net.bytebuddy.ByteBuddy;\nimport net.bytebuddy.description.modifier.Visibility;\nimport net.bytebuddy.implementation.FixedValue;\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.mockito.MockMakers;\nimport org.mockito.Mockito;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.lang.module.Configuration;\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleDescriptor;\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleFinder;\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleReader;\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleReference;\nimport java.net.URI;\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.Optional;\nimport java.util.Set;\nimport java.util.stream.Stream;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.withSettings;\n\npublic class ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest {\n    private static final String MODULE_NAME = \"mockito.test.module\";\n    private static final String HIDDEN_PACKAGE = \"sample.hidden\";\n    private static final String HIDDEN_TYPE_NAME = HIDDEN_PACKAGE + \".HiddenService\";\n    private static final String HIDDEN_TYPE_RESOURCE = \"sample/hidden/HiddenService.class\";\n\n    static {\n        System.setProperty(\"net.bytebuddy.experimental\", \"true\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void subclassMockMakerMocksTypeFromNonExportedNamedModule() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            Object mock = mockHiddenTypeFromNamedModule();\n\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception exception) {\n            Error unsupportedFeatureError = findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception);\n            if (unsupportedFeatureError == null) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static Object mockHiddenTypeFromNamedModule() throws Exception {\n        Class<?> hiddenType = loadHiddenTypeFromNamedModule();\n\n        assertThat(hiddenType.getModule().isNamed()).isTrue();\n        assertThat(hiddenType.getModule().isExported(HIDDEN_PACKAGE)).isFalse();\n\n        return Mockito.mock(hiddenType, withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.SUBCLASS));\n    }\n\n    private static Class<?> loadHiddenTypeFromNamedModule() throws ClassNotFoundException {\n        ModuleLayer parent = ModuleLayer.boot();\n        ModuleFinder finder = new InMemoryModuleFinder();\n        Configuration configuration =\n                parent.configuration().resolve(finder, ModuleFinder.of(), Set.of(MODULE_NAME));\n        ModuleLayer layer =\n                parent.defineModulesWithOneLoader(configuration, ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader());\n\n        return layer.findLoader(MODULE_NAME).loadClass(HIDDEN_TYPE_NAME);\n    }\n\n    private static Error findUnsupportedFeatureError(Throwable throwable) {\n        Throwable current = throwable;\n        while (current != null) {\n            if (current instanceof Error\n                    && NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError((Error) current)) {\n                return (Error) current;\n            }\n            current = current.getCause();\n        }\n        return null;\n    }\n\n    private static final class InMemoryModuleFinder implements ModuleFinder {\n        private final ModuleReference moduleReference;\n\n        private InMemoryModuleFinder() {\n            ModuleDescriptor descriptor =\n                    ModuleDescriptor.newModule(MODULE_NAME).packages(Set.of(HIDDEN_PACKAGE)).build();\n            moduleReference =\n                    new InMemoryModuleReference(\n                            descriptor, Map.of(HIDDEN_TYPE_RESOURCE, hiddenServiceBytes()));\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Optional<ModuleReference> find(String name) {\n            if (MODULE_NAME.equals(name)) {\n                return Optional.of(moduleReference);\n            }\n            return Optional.empty();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Set<ModuleReference> findAll() {\n            return Set.of(moduleReference);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] hiddenServiceBytes() {\n        return new ByteBuddy()\n                .subclass(Object.class)\n                .name(HIDDEN_TYPE_NAME)\n                .defineMethod(\"greeting\", String.class, Visibility.PUBLIC)\n                .intercept(FixedValue.value(\"real\"))\n                .make()\n                .getBytes();\n    }\n\n    private static final class InMemoryModuleReference extends ModuleReference {\n        private final Map<String, byte[]> resources;\n\n        private InMemoryModuleReference(ModuleDescriptor descriptor, Map<String, byte[]> resources) {\n            super(descriptor, URI.create(\"memory:///\" + descriptor.name()));\n            this.resources = resources;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public ModuleReader open() {\n            return new InMemoryModuleReader(resources);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class InMemoryModuleReader implements ModuleReader {\n        private final Map<String, byte[]> resources;\n\n        private InMemoryModuleReader(Map<String, byte[]> resources) {\n            this.resources = resources;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Optional<URI> find(String name) {\n            if (resources.containsKey(name)) {\n                return Optional.of(URI.create(\"memory:///\" + name));\n            }\n            return Optional.empty();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Optional<InputStream> open(String name) {\n            byte[] bytes = resources.get(name);\n            if (bytes == null) {\n                return Optional.empty();\n            }\n            return Optional.of(new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes));\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Optional<ByteBuffer> read(String name) {\n            byte[] bytes = resources.get(name);\n            if (bytes == null) {\n                return Optional.empty();\n            }\n            return Optional.of(ByteBuffer.wrap(bytes));\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void release(ByteBuffer byteBuffer) {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public Stream<String> list() {\n            return resources.keySet().stream();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void close() throws IOException {\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org_mockito.mockito_core;\\n\\nimport net.bytebuddy.ByteBuddy;\\nimport net.bytebuddy.description.modifier.Visibility;\\nimport net.bytebuddy.implementation.FixedValue;\\nimport org.graalvm.internal.tck.NativeImageSupport;\\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\\nimport org.mockito.MockMakers;\\nimport org.mockito.Mockito;\\n\\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\\nimport java.io.IOException;\\nimport java.io.InputStream;\\nimport java.lang.module.Configuration;\\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleDescriptor;\\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleFinder;\\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleReader;\\nimport java.lang.module.ModuleReference;\\nimport java.net.URI;\\nimport java.nio.ByteBuffer;\\nimport java.util.Map;\\nimport java.util.Optional;\\nimport java.util.Set;\\nimport java.util.stream.Stream;\\n\\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\\nimport static org.mockito.Mockito.withSettings;\\n\\npublic class ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest {\\n    private static final String MODULE_NAME = \\\"mockito.test.module\\\";\\n    private static final String HIDDEN_PACKAGE = \\\"sample.hidden\\\";\\n    private static final String HIDDEN_TYPE_NAME = HIDDEN_PACKAGE + \\\".HiddenService\\\";\\n    private static final String HIDDEN_TYPE_RESOURCE = \\\"sample/hidden/HiddenService.class\\\";\\n\\n    static {\\n        System.setProperty(\\\"net.bytebuddy.experimental\\\", \\\"true\\\");\\n    }\\n\\n    @Test\\n    void subclassMockMakerMocksTypeFromNonExportedNamedModule() throws Exception {\\n        try {\\n            Object mock = mockHiddenTypeFromNamedModule();\\n\\n            assertThat(Mockito.mockingDetails(mock).isMock()).isTrue();\\n        } catch (Error error) {\\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\\n                throw error;\\n            }\\n        } catch (Exception exception) {\\n            Error unsupportedFeatureError = findUnsupportedFeatureError(exception);\\n            if (unsupportedFeatureError == null) {\\n                throw exception;\\n            }\\n        }\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Object mockHiddenTypeFromNamedModule() throws Exception {\\n        Class<?> hiddenType = loadHiddenTypeFromNamedModule();\\n\\n        assertThat(hiddenType.getModule().isNamed()).isTrue();\\n        assertThat(hiddenType.getModule().isExported(HIDDEN_PACKAGE)).isFalse();\\n\\n        return Mockito.mock(hiddenType, withSettings().mockMaker(MockMakers.SUBCLASS));\\n    }\\n\\n    private static Class<?> loadHiddenTypeFromNamedModule() throws ClassNotFoundException {\\n        ModuleLayer parent = ModuleLayer.boot();\\n        ModuleFinder finder = new InMemoryModuleFinder();\\n        Configuration configuration =\\n                parent.configuration().resolve(finder, ModuleFinder.of(), Set.of(MODULE_NAME));\\n        ModuleLayer layer =\\n                parent.defineModulesWithOneLoader(configuration,