isibility. I wonder if adding try/catch for MockitoException could help handle potential path issues and ensure robustness.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating module descriptor issues**\\n\\nI’m considering a potential issue where the named module descriptor packages only include `sample.hidden`, but the carrier is defined in `org.mockito.codegen` within the source loader. Since the WRAPPER child has an unnamed module, it’s not part of the source module. I need to adjust the source module exports to connect the target hook using `targetLookup` via `carrier.getModule`. It looks like the generated probe, which is a child of the source loader, is calling `addExports` on the source module, obtaining it from `Class.forName(source.getName())`.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining instrumentation setup**\\n\\nI'm considering how instrumentation uses Mockito after setting it to static. It's important that global configurations come before Mockito in any test. I need to edit both aspects to make sure they're properly configured. I'm also wondering if the noUnsafe option affects Instrumentation; it might initialize plugins. This is definitely something I need to keep in mind while setting up the tests to ensure everything runs smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zyl4SAMa8o4BJUZmOx8wvNbN|fc_05eaf4290c8a1a6b016a21ad8d5d64819394124845877f8d29", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/MockitoTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "    static {\n        System.setProperty(\"net.bytebuddy.experimental\", \"true\");\n    }", "newText": "    static {\n        System.setProperty(\"net.bytebuddy.experimental\", \"true\");\n        System.setProperty(\"org.mockito.internal.noUnsafeInjection\", \"true\");\n    }"}]}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/MockitoTest.java\",\"edits\":[{\"oldText