[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the JPMS failure in:\n\n- `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/ModuleHandlerInnerModuleSystemFoundTest.java`\n\nRoot cause:\n- The test intentionally drives Mockito into the carrier path, where Mockito creates a carrier class in the source class loader’s unnamed module.\n- The generated module probe is defined in the named test module and tried to access that carrier, but the named module did not read its class loader’s unnamed module, causing:\n\n```text\nIllegalAccessError: module mockito.test.module does not read unnamed module\n```\n\nFix:\n- Switched module creation to use `ModuleLayer.Controller`.\n- Added a read edge from the in-memory named module to its class loader’s unnamed module before invoking Mockito:\n\n```java\ncontroller.addReads(hiddenType.getModule(), hiddenType.getClassLoader().getUnnamedModule());\n```\n\nThis keeps the test on a supported JPMS path while still exercising Mockito’s public subclass mock-maker API and the remaining carrier-related dynamic-access call sites.\n\nI did not run tests.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05eaf4290c8a1a6b016a21ae9b723481939c1ac5d1c51c5ede\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 525, "output": 224, "cacheRead": 47104, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 47853, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1780592279870, "responseId": "resp_05eaf4290c8a1a6b016a21ae99d0dc819399ca68b683059434"}}
